            'This self-regulating behaviour is why DC series motors were the universal choice for traction — trams, trains, trolleybuses — for over a century. No other motor type available in 1902 could match this combination of startup torque and smooth speed transition. Modern electric trains use AC motors with electronic inverters to achieve similar characteristics, but the old DC series motor did it with nothing but copper wire and iron.',
