            'Relative humidity (RH) measures how much water vapour the air is holding compared to the maximum it could hold at that temperature. At 50% RH, the air has half its maximum water capacity. At 95% RH (common during monsoons in Tamil Nadu), the air is nearly saturated. A peppercorn in 95% RH air will absorb water until its moisture content reaches about 14-16 percent — far above the safe storage level.',
